article.headline: Colorado State 88, Nebraska-Omaha 64
article.story:
OMAHA, Neb. (AP) -- Augustana College snapped a 10-game losing
streak to Nebraska-Omaha Saturday night, defeating the Mavericks
77-72 in North Central Conference action.

Joey Ryan led the Vikings (10-13 overall, 3-5 NCC) with 18
points. Mike Klepatz added 13 points and Nick Olson scored 11
points and gathered in 12 of his team's 35 rebounds.

Nebraska-Omaha (13-12, 2-5) was paced by 13 points apiece from
Ryan Curtis and Grant Nieland. Calvin Kapels scored 11 points and
grabbed 13 of the Mavericks' 40 boards.

Augustana scored 34 points in the paint to 28 points for
Nebraska-Omaha. The Vikings led 34-29 at halftime.
